 <div class="table-responsive"> 
  <table class="wiki_table"> 
   <tbody> 
    <tr> 
     <th style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"> <h2>Shard Spiral</h2> </th> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"><img style="width: 200px; height: 200px;" title="Shard Spiral" src="/file/Elden-Ring/shard_spiral_sorcery_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png" alt="shard spiral sorcery elden ring wiki guide 200px" width="200" height="200"></td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td>Spell Type</td> 
     <td><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Glintstone Sorceries" href="/Glintstone+Sorceries" target="">Glintstone Sorceries</a></td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td>FP Cost 14</td> 
     <td>Slots Used&nbsp;1</td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td colspan="2"><img title="item_effect_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_18px" src="/file/Elden-Ring/item_effects_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_55px_18px.png" alt="item effects icon elden ring wiki guide 55px 18px" width="18" height="18">Effect 
      <div class="lineleft">
        Fire twin spiraling projectiles 
      </div> <br><img style="float: left;" title="Attributes Requirement" src="/file/Elden-Ring/attributes-required-elden-ring-wiki-guide-18.png" alt="attributes required elden ring wiki guide 18" width="18" height="18">Requires 
      <div class="lineleft"> 
       <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Intelligence" href="/Intelligence" target="">Intelligence</a>&nbsp;27 
       <br> 
       <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Faith" href="/Faith" target="">Faith</a> 0 
       <br> 
       <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Arcane" href="/Arcane" target="">Arcane</a>&nbsp;0 
      </div> </td> 
    </tr> 
   </tbody> 
  </table> 
 </div> 
</div> 
<p><strong>Shard Spiral </strong> is a&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Sorceries" href="/Sorceries" target="">Sorcery</a> in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. <strong>Shard Spiral spell</strong>&nbsp;is a ranged projectile magic spell&nbsp;that is used in combat. Updated to <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Patch Notes" href="/Patch+Notes">Patch 1.07</a>.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>One of the glintstone sorceries of the Academy of Raya Lucaria.</em></p> 
 <p><em>Fires twin projectiles that form a spiral as they travel. This sorcery can be cast repeatedly and while in motion.</em><br><em>Charging enhances potency.</em></p> 
 <p><em>A sorcery of the Karolos Conspectus, the most venerable of the academy. This was the product of a failed attempt to create a new comet.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to find Shard Spiral</h3> 
<p>Where to find <strong>Shard Spiral </strong>:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Available for purchase from the Sorcery Instruction of <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Sorceress Sellen" href="/Sorceress+Sellen" target="">Sorceress Sellen</a> for 8000<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="13" height="13"> after progressing through her questline and choosing to side with her.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring&nbsp;Shard Spiral Guide</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Glintstone Sorceries" href="/Glintstone+Sorceries">Glintstone Sorcery</a></li> 
 <li>Stamina Cost: 28</li> 
 <li>Deals magic damage</li> 
 <li>The primary draw of this sorcery is its use against larger targets. When cast, the spiraling pair of magic bolts will slowly fly toward their target and then continue to fly through them instead of exploding on contact. The magic bolts will continue to deal damage as they fly through the target until they reach their maximum range, at which point the bolts expire. As such, this sorcery can do considerably more damage than many other sorceries, provided the magic bolts are allowed to travel through their target as long as possible.</li> 
 <li>Faster cast time (especially when uncharged) and lower FP cost than other high damage sorceries, more equivalent to Great Glintstone Shard in terms of speed and cost 
  <ul> 
   <li>The drawback is its slow travel time and moderate damage against smaller enemies</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li><em><span style="color: #ff6600;">NOTE</span>: This&nbsp;</em><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Glintstone Sorceries" href="/Glintstone+Sorceries">Glintstone Sorcery</a><em>&nbsp;was changed with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Patch Notes" href="/Patch+Notes">Patch 1.07</a>&nbsp;as follows: The Attack Power was Increased.</em></li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
