				<li id="16642854" class="cmnt-root" data="7" data-d="1650598110000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579649/Shard-Spiral" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">21 Apr 2022 23:28</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16642854" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Maybe THE most slept on pvp spell. The tracking is insane and the long projectiles combined with the slow speed really messed with people. This is pretty much my go-to spam during the opening and whenever I ever get a lot of distance from the enemy. I&apos;ll throw out 4 or 5 and unless they turn around and run or have Blood Hound Step, its guaranteed to land a couple hits on roll catches alone. But thats not even the best part about it. If they happen to dodge straight into it, IT WILL LOOP AROUND AND HIT THEM IN THE BACK. I mostly like to duel and I can&apos;t tell you how great it is watching white mask ROB scrubs get drilled in the back, usually leaving them with little to no hp, right when they thought it was safe to start spamming L2. TLDR its insane for pvp</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16642854" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16642854" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">1</span>)</a><di